The paper deals with association rule mining, which is a common task in machine learning and data mining. The use of maximum entropy probability estimates is a technique that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and databases (cs.DB). Given the focus on probabilistic modeling and data analysis, cs.LG and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DS, cs.AI, and cs.DB.
